@node "Intro" "How this story began"

 One of my colleague (Edina Horváth) brought once a quite nice logical
game into our office. It was a russian program, written for IBM-PC
soapboxes under DOS. I found it very amusing, so I took it home. Under the
PC emulator it was @{fg shine}soooo@{fg text} slow! (Probably written in some kind of old Pascal
version...)
 I showed it to my girlfriend (who is not my girlfriend anymore, but this
text is not about us), and that was hardly a good idea at all... :) She
just LOVED that game, but it took about half an our while she played a
round. So I could leave my two women together for at least an hour in pair
alone. (My ex-girlfriend and my Amiga.) After a while I got rid of the situation,
and I looked for an Amiga clone for this game on Aminet. I found one, but it
was an altered version, did not behave similar in all rules, written in AMOS,
and after all I did not liked it very much. The other reason was: I got some new
ideas to be implemented.
 Let's start from scrach then... And I wrote it. There is a possibility to
play under the original rules, but extended rules give more pleasure I think.
 Now my ex-girfriend was still playing at least an hour, but now she could complete
4-6 games... She is unbeatable in the high scores... :)

@endnode

